<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Viag Posts 20 Percent Rise in Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The German industrial holding
conglomerate Viag said today its pre-tax profits reached 2.19
billion marks (1.27 billion U.S. dollars) in the first nine months
this year, up 20 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The conglomerate's turnover in September rose 18 percent to
36.58 billion marks. Viag expected the overall figure for the year
1997 would top 50 billion marks.
</P>
<P>
The turnover growth was achieved despite some early start-up
losses in telecommunications operations, and half the growth came
from newly-acquired holdings during the period in which it had
invested 6.1 billion marks, Viag said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from telecommunications, Viag also has stakes in energy,
chemicals, packaging, and logistics companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
