<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Police Arrest Three Involved in Killing of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan police have already
arrested three people who were involved in killings of Iranian
cadets in mid-September but the main culprit was still at large, a
senior police official said today.
</P>
<P>
The three accused, identified as Asif, Yaqoob Mughal and Qari
Saddique, would be handed over to the anti-terrorist court for
speedy trial, said Rao Muhammad Iqbal, Senior Superintendent of
Police Rawalpindi, the sister city of Islamabad, at a news
conference.
</P>
<P>
The three accused during the interrogation had confessed their
involvement in killings of the three Iranian technicians on
September 17 in Rawalpindi, Iqbal said.
</P>
<P>
However, he admitted that main culprit and the conspirator of
the tragedy Ajmal Akram Lahori along with another co-accused
Rashid were still at large.
</P>
<P>
Further investigation in the case would continue until the
arrest of remaining two culprits, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
