<HEADLINE> Philippines Sets Seven-Point Agenda for APEC Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines has set a
seven-point agenda to pursue at the annual Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) meetings in Canada starting next week, the
Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the Foreign Affairs Department as saying that
the Philippines sees the APEC meetings "as a forum to advance its
goals and objectives for economic development."
</P>
<P>
Objectives of the seven-point Philippine agenda include
elevation to a higher level and intensification of economic and
technical cooperation among APEC member economies.
</P>
<P>
The goals also contain eliciting a timely and adequate APEC
response to the ongoing currency turmoil in Southeast Asia and
pushing APEC further to serve as active prime mover for global
liberalization.
</P>
<P>
Others aims are sustainable APEC role in making a difference to
business, further infrastructure development, building up APEC
capabilities for emergency preparedness and sustained drive
towards the vision of an Asia-Pacific community.
</P>
<P>
The department said the Philippines will push for more
cooperative development efforts in economic infrastructure in the
APEC meetings under the forum's Framework on Economic Cooperation
and Development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
