<HEADLINE> Vietnam Seeks to Further Ties with Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam would like to strengthen
and develop friendly and cooperative relations with Cambodia,
Vietnamese Prime Minister Pan Van Khai said here today.
</P>
<P>
Pan made the remark while meeting Cambodian First Prime
Minister Ung Huot who was here to attend the seventh summit of the
Francophone nations.
</P>
<P>
Pan said the Vietnamese government and the people
support Cambodia's entry into the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN), the Vietnam News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Pan said the internal affairs of Cambodia should be handled by
the Cambodian people themselves.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the Cambodian government and people,
under the leadership of King Norodom Sihanouk, would overcome all
difficulties and build Cambodia into a peaceful, neutral and
prosperous country.
</P>
<P>
Ung Huot highly valued Vietnam's support for Cambodia's entry
into ASEAN. He expressed his belief that the cooperation between
the two countries should be expanded in many fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
