<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Continues Visit in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGOYA, Japan, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Governor of Japan's
Aichi Prefecture Leigi Suzuki today extended his whole-hearted
welcome to Chinese Premier Li Peng who arrived here this afternoon
to continue his visit to Japan.
</P>
<P>
At a banquet held in honor of the Chinese premier, Suzuki said
exchanges between Aichi Prefecture and China could be traced to a
long time ago.
</P>
<P>
He said the prefecture now enjoys a relationship of friendly
provinces with Jiangsu Province of China, established in 1980, and
Nagoya in the prefecture enjoys a relationship of friendly cities
with Nanjing of Jiangsu Province, established in 1978.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation between the prefecture and various
provinces in China are thriving with many key enterprises in the
prefecture such as the Toyato Motor Corp. now undertaking quite a
few joint-venture projects in China, said Suzuki.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor and Minister in Charge of State Commission of
Science and Technology Song Jian spoke at the banquet on behalf of
Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Song said the Chinese premier's current visit to Japan has
helped increase mutual understanding and expand common ground
between China and Japan, which will promote the healthy and steady
development of the Sino-Japanese good-neighborly friendship and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said economic and trade cooperation and exchanges in science
and technology and culture between Jiangsu Province of China and
Aichi Prefecture have gained marked progress and that Nagoya, as
the place of origin of the famous "Ping-pong Diplomacy" in the
1970s, is well known to many Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the prefecture will make greater contributions to
the cause of Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
Before attending the banquet, the Chinese premier visited
Toyato Motor Corp.. He is expected to visit Osaka and Nara.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng arrived in Tokyo Tuesday for a six-day official
good-will visit to Japan. While in Tokyo, he paid a visit to
Nippon Electric Co., Ltd and Honda Motor Co., Ltd.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
