Baghdad today following Iraq's decision Thursday to order six
American members to leave Iraq immediately.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and her British
counterpart Robin Cook held talks in Edinburgh, Scotland today on
the U.N.-Iraq crisis and issued a dire warning to Iraqi President
Saddam Hussein that he is making a "grave" mistake.
</P>
