<HEADLINE> UK Gov't to Change National Health Service Radically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The British government is
planning radical changes to the National Health Service (NHS),
bringing an end to the internal market.
</P>
<P>
A forthcoming legislation on the health and welfare system
would propose new bodies to run local services as well as new
national agencies to improve standards of care and provide new
drugs and treatments, said local press reports.
</P>
<P>
The White Paper, which will be published by the end of the
year, will set out different models of how NHS could be organized,
but reports said the government intends to change the service step
by step.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the new legislation, family doctors and
health organizations will be given a key role in shaping services
through so-called locality commissioning groups.
</P>
<P>
A new agency will offer national guidance on drugs and
treatments, and another new national body will monitor quality
standards.
</P>
<P>
The existing fundholding scheme on NHS, introduced by the
previous Conservative government, will be phased out. 
</P>
