next 24 or 48 hours would determine what the next moves would be,
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Annan said he expected the Security
Council to take a firm stand on the recent crisis over the weapons
inspection in Iraq the Council had done.
</P>
