<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 14 (Xinhua) -- One person has been killed and
several people have been kidnapped so far by a gangster who robbed
a bank in the western Germany state of North Rhine-Westphalia this
afternoon and is still chased by police at the moment, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
According to police authorities in the city of Essen, the
unidentified gangster, armed with a pistol, and possibly also a
rifle, robbed a bank in Bocholt near Essen at about 4:00 pm today.
</P>
<P>
He has changed several cars during his flight and has taken
their drivers hostage one after another.
</P>
<P>
After a serious traffic accident later, the gangster tried to
stop another car and killed its 33-year-old driver who had denied
to surrender.
</P>
<P>
Latest reports said that German police have lost trace of the
gangster after he fled into the Netherlands in the evening.
</P>
