<HEADLINE> GA President on UN Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Hennadiy Udovenko,
President of the General Assembly of the United Nations stressed
here today that the successful conclusion of the first stage of
the consideration of the Secretary-General's report with a
consensus resolution was a major step forward in the
Organization's reform.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the reporters, President Udovenko said the
resolution adopted Tuesday signalled the strong political
commitment of the entire membership to reform the United Nations,
and it showed existing differences of the member states did not
stand in the way of meaningful transformations.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko said the resolution gave unprecedented exposure to the
positions of individual members and groups of states on a broad
range of practical matters related to the process of the reform.
</P>
<P>
The president said it represented a clear endorsement of the
Secretary-General's efforts and initiatives aimed at modernizing
the organization.
</P>
<P>
he said the resolution helped to develop synergy and solidify the
partnership between the Secretary-General and the membership on
an issue of direct and vital interest to every state.
</P>
<P>
The president said the General Assembly had made a number of
important decisions already, but he would postpone until
December a broad review of its highlights. 
</P>
