<HEADLINE> Myanmar Carries Out Major Government Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar carried out a major
reshuffle of cabinet ministers today following the formation of
the State Peace and Development Council (SPDC), a new governing
body replacing the former State Law and Order Restoration Council
(SLORC).
</P>
<P>
In the 39-member new cabinet, Senior-General Than Shwe still
holds posts of prime minister and defense minister, while the
posts of two deputy prime ministers remain unchanged, according to
an official announcement this evening.
</P>
<P>
Over a dozen new ministers were appointed in the cabinet
including two for new added ministries -- the Ministry of Military
Affairs and the Ministry of Electric Power.
</P>
<P>
Former senior cabinet ministers and a few former SLORC members
have been placed in a 14-member advisory body to the SPDC.
</P>
<P>
The SLORC was formed in September 1988 when it took over the
power of state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
