<HEADLINE> Exploration Team of China Leaves for South Pole </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 15 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese exploration team
left here today for the South Pole to begin China's 14th
scientific survey of the region.
</P>
<P>
The team will spend four months conducting in-depth research
on the South Pole.
</P>
<P>
The 145-member team, which consists of 140 experts and support
personnel, and five reporters, departed from Shanghai aboard the
ship "Xue Long", which is scheduled to return to Shanghai in early
April next year.
</P>
<P>
Two Russian and two Japanese scientists also went to the South
Pole on the same ship.
</P>
<P>
The team will conduct scientific research in glaciers,
construction of ports and installation of satellite receivers and
color digital imaging systems.
</P>
<P>
The team will also construct sewage disposal systems at the
Chinese Great Wall and Zhongshan stations.
</P>
<P>
China Pacific Insurance Company Ltd. will ensure the vessel and
provide personal injury insurance for the team members, with total
premiums totalling 100 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
