<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Improves River Navigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 15 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hunan Province
has adopted advanced technology and installed high-tech equipment
to prevent accidents on its rivers.
</P>
<P>
Hunan technicians installed highly sensitive advanced equipment
in all the lighthouses in the province, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The Dongting Lake and the province's four main rivers have combined
navigation channels of over 10,000 kilometers. Silting and
low-level navigation management led to a number of accidents over
the years, said the local officials.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has allocated over 200 million yuan
(24 million US dollars) for technological development programs
since the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
New channel markers have been placed on the Dongting Lake and solar
cells have been installed in over 100,000 lighthouses.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that ships carrying over 130 million tons of
goods ply the navigation channels in the province annually, with
the total volume representing a dramatic rise on the 30 million
tons in the past. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
