<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Campaign to Clean Up Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will launch a campaign
in the coming months to clean up white pollution.
</P>
<P>
One step city officials plan to take is the installation of a
network of trash cans along main streets and in residential
districts.
</P>
<P>
In another step, non-recyclable shopping bags will be phased
out in department stores, groceries and open markets.
</P>
<P>
Beijing also will target disposable plastic foam containers. A
citywide recovery rate has been set at 30 percent, but some major
areas will be required to meet a 100 percent standard.
</P>
<P>
Barbecues and posters that clutter city streets are also
included in the anti-litter campaign.
</P>
<P>
The white pollution clean-up drive is one of many environmental
protection efforts launched this year in Beijing. Previous
clean-up campaigns have addressed the issue of pollution and
litter in 10 rivers, several roadways and railway
right-of-ways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
