<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1400 GMT, November 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Myanmar today formed the State Peace and Development
Council as its new governing body of the country, replacing the
State Law and Order Restoration Council (SLORC), according to an
official announcement this evening. (Myanmar-New Governing
Body-Urgent)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said
today Asians and their Asian values would contribute to the Global
Century because they believe in prospering others in order to
prosper themselves, the Malaysian national news agency Bernama
reported. (BC-Malaysia-Mahathir-Asian Values)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Asian and European representatives Friday called
for a stronger cooperation between Asia and Europe in the field
of investment.
</P>
<P>
"Investment is an important and inseparable part of the overall
economic relationship between Asia and Europe," the
representatives said in a chairman's statement released at the end
of the Second Asia-Europe Business Forum (AEBF ii) here on
Friday.(Thailand-Asia-Europe-Investment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) has
officially decided to boycott the Middle East and North Africa
economic conference due to open Sunday in Qatar to protest
Israel's derailment of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The decision to boycott the regional economic conference to be
held in Qatari capital Doha was made at a three-hour PNA Cabinet
meeting held in the West Bank city of Ramallah Friday
night. (Palestine-Doha Conference-Boycott)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Travelers from yellow fever endemic countries
will need a vaccination certificate recognized by the World
Health Organization (WHO) to enter Malaysia, its Health Minister
Chua JUI Meng said today. (Malaysia-Yellow Fever) 
</P>
