<HEADLINE> Fifth China Drama Festival Opens in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth China Drama
Festival opened here today amidst a joyous atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 artists from 22 troupes are attending the festival,
during which 22 plays from 15 genre of drama will be staged.
</P>
<P>
The festival will feature the most recent developments in
dramatic creation and performances, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The 14th Plum Blossom Awards will be presented during the
festival to 21 artists from the Beijing Opera Theater of Shanghai,
the Guangdong Opera Troupe in Guangzhou and various other
troupes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
