<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Visits Russian Treasures Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li
Lanqing this evening visited the Russian Treasures Exhibition now
being held in the China Art Gallery here.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, State Councillor and Minister in Charge of the
State Commission for Economic Restructuring, among other leaders,
also visited the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
In the company of Russian Ambassador to China Igor A. Rogachev,
Li Lanqing looked closely at almost all the 1,590 pieces of
exhibits in the three exhibition halls. Li kept nodding
his appreciation for the craftsmanship of the precious and exquisite
artifacts and spoke highly of the long history of Russian
civilization.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is the largest exhibition of Russian treasures
ever held outside Russia and two-third of the objects have never
been displayed even in Russia itself. They include a natural gold
nugget weighing 1,461.8 grams, a 46-kg gold ball fashioned in
1890, and dozens of the world's most precious medallions.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is joinly sponsored by the China Association for
International Friendly Contact and the Gochran of Russia, an
entity directly under the supervision of the Russian Ministry of
Finance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
