<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jia Wins Third Gold at Fina World Junior Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 15 (Xinhua) -- China's Hu Jia captured
his third gold medal after winning the boy's one-meter springboard
event on the fourth day of the 11th Fina World Junior Diving
Championship here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hu collected 354.39 points in the 14-15 years age group to beat
Canada's Etienne Gauthier with 346.56 into second spot while
Patrick Rodriguez Rubio was third with 338.67.
</P>
<P>
In the girl's platform event of the 16-18 age group, Canada's
Emilie Heymans won the gold with a total score of 405.21 points
while teammate Alida Diplacido took the silver with 381.9.
</P>
<P>
Swede Anna Lindberg finished third with 363.9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
