<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts International Broadcast Music Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The International Broadcast
Music Festival opened today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The festival, the sixth event of its kind held in Shanghai, is
sponsored by the Shanghai Oriental Broadcasting Station. This
year's festival, the city's largest ever music festival, has
attracted representatives from 164 broadcast stations and
companies in more than 30 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Some 110 music programs will compete for the "Golden
Chimes Award". The festival's appraisal committee includes nine
broadcasters from Australia, the United States, Japan, Franc,
Egypt, Mexico, Germany, and China.
</P>
<P>
The five-day festival will feature an international academic
symposium on trans-century broadcast music, and an international
fair of audio and video products, acoustic products and music
books, as well as an exhibition of oriental folk music collections
and the selection of China's most outstanding broadcast music
anchors.
</P>
<P>
Famous Chinese and foreign orchestras, bands, song and dance
ensembles, and singers will perform during the festival, which
will also feature the city's largest ever open-air evening gala.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
