<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Expands Border Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Province in northeast
China generated an import-export volume of 104.97 million US
dollars from border trade in the first eight months of this year,
up 15 percent on last yea's same period.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounted for eight percent of the province's total
foreign trade volume.
</P>
<P>
Jilin shares a 232.7-km border with Russia and a 1,206-km border
with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Border trade, which was once dominated by a dozen
state-owned trade companies, is now carried out by over 100
companies in various trade sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
