<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Forms New Governing Body to Replace SLORC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar today formed the State
Peace and Development Council as its new governing body of the
country, replacing the State Law and Order Restoration Council
(SLORC), according to an official announcement this evening.
</P>
<P>
The new council was made up of 19 members including four
leaders of the SLORC with Senior-General Than Shwe as chairman,
General Maung Aye as vice-chairman, lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt
as first secretary and Lieutenant-General Tin Oo as second
secretary.
</P>
<P>
Other members of the new council include commanders of various
military regions.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said the move is in the interests of "a full
democratic system in the country and a peaceful, prosperous and
developed nation."
</P>
<P>
The SLORC was formed in September 1988 when it took over the
power of state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
