<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Funds Invested in Chinese Province's Animal Husbandry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province has invested 760 million yuan (95 million U.S. dollars)
in 27 animal husbandry projects, including 40 million U.S. dollar
of foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
These funds are mainly loans from international financial
organizations or foreign governments and direct overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
The province also has introduced advanced scientific technology
and expertise with the purpose of increasing the output of poultry
and livestock.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the province improved its stock of cattle
by 11 percent; pigs, 77.6 percent; and poultry, 67.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
So far, the output of animal husbandry has accounted for more
than 35 percent of the province's total agricultural output and
the sector has become a pillar industry of the province's
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
