<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Booming in Eastern China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The Wuxi New District in
Jiangsu Province has become a popular foreign investment spot in
this eastern China province.
</P>
<P>
So far, 161 overseas-funded enterprises have been set up in the
district, involving an overseas investment of 1.1 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The district includes the Wuxi National High-Tech Development
Zone and the Wuxi Singapore Technology Park.
</P>
<P>
The pace of introducing overseas funds has quickened since the
beginning of this year, and 40 projects are expected to be
approved in the next two months, with 250 million U.S. dollars of
investment from Japan, the United States, Malaysia, Germany and
Taiwan, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
