<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 Killed in Car Crashes in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were
killed and 14 others injured in two separate road accidents
Friday night in South Africa, South African Press Association
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Six people were killed in the first accident in the Northern
Cape province when their vehicle overturned and burst into
flames.
</P>
<P>
Four men died at the scene, while two died on the way to
hospital, police said. Four other people were seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
In another accident later on the day, five were killed and 10
wounded when their mini-bus taxi left the road and rolled over a
cliff in Free State.
</P>
<P>
Free State police spokesman Leon van Rooyen said police were
investigating the possibility that one of the vehicle's tires
burst before the driver lost control of the taxi.
</P>
<P>
The mini-bus crashed into a barrier before falling over the
cliff at about 10:20 p.m. (2020 GMT). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
