<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-US Technology Center Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-US Energy and
Environmental Technologies Center, jointly funded by the
governments of China and the United States, opened today at
Qinghua University in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Officials from China's State Science and Technology Commission
and the U.S. Department of Energy attended today's ceremony, along
with experts from Qinghua University and Tulan University in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The aforementioned government agencies reached a 1995 agreement
to improve and protect the global environment by promoting
exchanges of advanced energy and environmental technologies
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The center will focus on the research and development of
technology to produce clean coal, maximize the efficient use of
energy and renewable resources, and promote environmental
protection, according to Wu Zongxin, director of the center.
</P>
</TEXT>
