<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila OKs Zero-Tariff Importation of White Corn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today approved the zero-tariff importation of 50,000 tons of
white corn grits, 10 percent of which is for human consumption.
</P>
<P>
The importation will be used to stabilize the prices of corn
grits, the staple food of people in the Visayas region, the
central part of the country which will be adversely affected by
supply shortage due to the El Nino weather phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Asking for the president's approval, Agriculture Secretary
Salvador Escudero said the importation is expected to arrive
between December 1997 and January 1998 and will be sold to corn
millers.
</P>
<P>
The balance of the imported corn would be sold to industrial
users but the selling price will include 35 percent of the landed
cost, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
