<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Airlines Receives First A320 Airliner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Airlines has become
the recipient of an A320 airliner from the European Airbus
Industrie.
</P>
<P>
The airplane landed recently at Jianqiao Airport in Hangzhou, a
scenic city in east China, after a flight from Bangkok, capital of
Thailand, according to the latest issue of China Aviation News.
</P>
<P>
This is the first of five A320s to be introduced by the
airline. These airliners will be put into use on air routes from
Hangzhou to Guangzhou, Qingdao, Fuzhou, Xiamen, Shenzhen, Beijing
and other cities, the paper said.  
</P>
