<HEADLINE> Swiss Andy Hofmann Wins Macao 31st Motorcycle Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Veteran Swiss rider Andy Hofmann
won the 31st Macao Motorcycle Grand Prix by finishing the 10-lap
race at an average speed of 140.61 kilometers per hour here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old Swiss road racer, who qualified in pole
position, won the single-leg, 10-lap race on his 750cc Kawasaki,
beating last year's winner Ulsterman Phillip McCallen on the 500cc
Miller Racing Yamaha into second place.
</P>
<P>
The race had to be cut from its customary 15 laps because of
two suspensions following a false start by British rider David
Goodley and a crash by French rider Eric Gomez.
</P>
<P>
Hofmann, three-time German superbike champion, finished sixth
and third in two previous appearances in Macao. He set the
fastest lap record of 2:32:88 in the final qualifying race on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Phillip McCallen, 33, won the second place while Shawn Higbee
of the United States on his 900cc Graves Motor Sports finished
third.
</P>
<P>
The race was held under partly cloudy but dry weather
conditions on Macao's bendy 6.2 kilometer Guia street circuit.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
