<HEADLINE> Ballroom Dancing Becomes Popular in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Ballroom dancing, introduced
to China 11 years ago, has become one of the favorite pastimes of
Beijing citizens, according to the Beijing Ballroom Association.
</P>
<P>
Many citizens get together automatically for social dancing on
the street sides and squares at dawn and dust, the association
reported. More and more residents, unsatisfied with
self-entertainment, have enrolled in ballroom-dance training
classes with hopes of competing in professional and amateur
contests.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 special schools teach ballroom dancing in Beijing
and about 50,000 people have been trained, according to the
association.
</P>
<P>
Beijing TV and the Beijing Ballroom Association have announced
that TV media in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Wuhan will
organize a ballroom-dance competition. enditem
nnnn
</P>
