<HEADLINE> China Compiles Real Estate Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- China is compiling a real
estate market index to determine development trends in the sector,
according to a recent issue of "China Information".
</P>
<P>
The index, scheduled for completion by the end of this year,
will summarize real estate prices in 35 major cities. The State
Planning Commission and the State Statistical Bureau will jointly
compile the index which will be announced in January, April, July
and October of each year.
</P>
<P>
China's real estate sector attracted investments of 324.7
billion yuan in 1996, including foreign investments of some 6.5
billion US dollars. 
</P>
