<HEADLINE> England Retains World Squash Team Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 15 (Xinhua) -- England defeated Canada
3-0 to retain the Men's World Squash Team Championships title here
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
England's Simon Parke showed his superb form by crushing
Canadian Jonathon Power 9-0, 9-1, 9-1 in just 18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Parke said he was satisfied with his performance in the team
championships, having defeated newly-crowned world individual
champion Rodney Eyles of Australia on Friday.
</P>
<P>
England's Chris Walker made sure of the title when he brushed
aside Gary Waite 9-1, 9-3, 9-4 while in the dead rubber, Del
Harris defeated Graham Ryding 9-1, 9-1. 
</P>
