<HEADLINE> Nigerians Assured of Visa for France '98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The French Embassy in Lagos on
Friday assured Nigeria's national team Super Eagles and its fans
of visa grants to enable them appear at the France '98 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The European Union and the Commonwealth of Nations imposed
sports sanctions against Nigeria after its government executed
author Ken Saro-Wiwa and eight other minority activists on charges
of murdur in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
After Nigeria qualified for the French World Cup, both the
French Organizing Committee and FIFA have stated that they will
not tolerate politicking, but some European countries have
threatened to prevent Nigeria from going to France.
</P>
<P>
The assurance of visa by the French Embassy is a great relief
to the worrying Nigerian football authority, who will now happily
go ahead in their preparations for the French summer. 
</P>
