<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-grade Highway Leads to Dazu Stone Carvings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- A high-grade road is being
built to link Chongqing, China's largest municipality, with the
Dazu Stone Carvings, a world-class tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
Funded with 248 million yuan (29.879 million US dollars) by
investors from Chongqing and Hong Kong, the road will be 30.39
kilometers in length, 15 meters in width, with a designed capacity
of 80 kilometers per hour. The road is expected to open to traffic
by 1998.
</P>
<P>
Located in Dazu County of Chongqing, the Dazu Stone Carvings
were built over a 1,000 years from the Five Dynasties (907-960) to
the Song Dynasty (960-1279). The over 50,000 carvings are
scattered over 100 spots in the county, with the most famous being
the cliff statues in Beishan and Baodingshan areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
