<HEADLINE> New Shipping Route Links Ningbo with Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO (Zhejiang), November 12 (Xinhua) -- The French container
ship "Gemina" arrived at Beilun Port recently, marking a new
weekly route. The route, which was opened by French CMA
Corporation, links China's city of Ningbo to Europe.
</P>
<P>
As France's largest shipping company, CMA plans to operate nine
fourth-generation container ships on the route, which passes Hong
Kong, Singapore, Jeddah and Port Said, with ships anchoring at Le
Havre, Hamburg, Thames Port and Rotterdam. The return trip takes
63 days.
</P>
<P>
Beilun Port in Ningbo is the only port on China's mainland
capable of accommodating container ships of the fourth and fifth
generation, with a handling capacity of 800,000 TEUs (twenty-foot
equivalent containers). Ningbo Port, which includes Beilun Port,
is the third largest on China's mainland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
