<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Rocks Hokkaido </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 15 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake registering 6.0
on the open-ended Richter scale jolted the eastern part of Japan's
northernmost prefecture of Hokkaido today, the Meteorological Agency
said.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of casualties or damage. No tsunami or tidal
wave warnings were issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at around 4:05 p.m. was focused about
150 kilometers under the seabed in the Nemuro region, eastern
Hokkaido, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
At 1:42 p.m., another quake measuring 5.4 on the Richter scale hit
northern and eastern Japan, according to the agency. 
</P>
