<HEADLINE> Asian Values Contribute to Global Century: Mahathir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said today Asians and their Asian values would
contribute to the Global Century because they believe in
prospering others in order to prosper themselves, the Malaysian
national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir described the 21st century as the "Global Century"
rather than the Asian Century.
</P>
<P>
However, it is the Asian values that would help the Global
Century become reality, "for we do not believe in destroying
others, undermining them deliberately, doing shady things in order
to ensure that they fail," he said today at a function in
Langkawi, a resort island, some 500 kilometers north from here.
</P>
<P>
"Nor do we gloat obscenely when we see others suffer as a
result of our actions," he added.
</P>
<P>
"These Asian values will not only overcome the present problem
but will actually help us to be magnanimous to those who try to
disable us. Thus will the Global Century be brought about," he was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
On the present financial woes facing Southeast Asia, Mahathir
said the woes were due to greedy foreign traders who decided to
take everything for themselves and in the process, impoverishing
their host partners.
</P>
<P>
He said such traders neither practiced smart partnership nor
took a long-term view.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said such a partnership was exploitative and the host
country should avoid this type of investors.
</P>
<P>
"If allowed to invest, they should be restricted...the source
of their funds must be carefully examined," he stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
