<HEADLINE> China to Start 2nd-Phase Resettlement in Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The 4-day State Council Three
Gorges Resettlement Working Conference concluded here today, which
called for efforts to complete the second-phase resettlement of
residents, and ensure the successful operation of the first group
of power generators by 2003.
</P>
<P>
In his keynote speech to the conference, vice-premier Zou
Jiahua reviewed the achievements made in the resettlement of
residents as well as support from all fields for the Three Gorges
project.
</P>
<P>
He said that since 1993 the State has arranged funds totalling
8.575 billion yuan for the relocation of residents in the areas,
resettling a total of 820,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The State Council has worked out a series of preferential
policies encouraging support for the resettlement and economic
development in the areas, the vice-premier said.
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 971 supporting projects for the resettlement
of residents have been completed, drawing funds totalling 1.863
billion yuan. And some 199 "hope" schools have been set up with
aiding funds.
</P>
<P>
The just-concluded conference has put forward the general goal
of the second-phase resettlement: resettle a total population of
500,000.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, the vice-premier called for priority to be given
to handling of the relations between resettlement and economic
development, technical renovation of enterprises relocated,
agricultural development in the reservoir area, and protection of
the ecological environment and cultural relics in the process of
relocation. 
</P>
