<HEADLINE> Heavy Fog Grounds Airliners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- A heavy fog grounded 108
flights from Beijing to other cities Friday involving thousands of
passengers, and the airport is as busy as usual today.
</P>
<P>
Except the only punctual takeoff of an Air China jet plane
early Friday morning, all other flights to Dalian, Tianyuan,
Luoyang and other destinations were delayed, said an official from
the Beijing International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Airport officials timely reported flight information to delayed
passengers and also provided food for them.
</P>
<P>
According to information released by the airport, all flights
resumed normal operation at noon yesterday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
