<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts Symposium on Children's Literature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 15 (Xinhua) -- A three-day national
symposium on writing and publishing children's literature opened
today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the symposium will discuss wide-ranging topics
related to children's literature, including the publication of
reading materials, characteristics and problems related to writing
and development trends in the industry. The goal of the symposium
is to promote the development of children's literature produced in
China to a new stage, as well as to provide more and better
reading materials for youngsters.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to write and publish children's literature have
produced promising results, with a number of literary works having
won national and international awards in recent years. 
