<HEADLINE> Hingis Advances to Semifinals at U.S. Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis
Friday night advanced to the semifinals at the 450,000 U.S.
dollars Advanda Championship by beating German qualifier Anke
Huber 7-6 (10- 8), 5-7, 6-4, at Villanova, Pennsylvania.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss teenage is now 72-4 on the year. She improved to 7-1
lifetime against Huber, who took a 3-1 lead in the first set
before Hingis rallied to send it into a tiebreak. Hingis took a
5-3 advantage in the tiebreak, but Huber won the next three points.
</P>
<P>
Huber won the last four games of the second set to even the
match and then broke serve to start the deciding set. But Hingis
won five of the last seven games.
</P>
<P>
Hingis joins fifth-seeded Lindsay Davenport, eighth seed
Aranxta Sanchez Vicario and seventh-seeded Irina Spirlea in the
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Davenport defeated second-seed and defending champion Jana
Novotna 6-3, 6-2. Davenport, who won her sixth WTA title last week
in Chicago, moved to No. 2 in the world with Friday's win.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario eliminated third seed Amanda Coetzer 6-2, 6-2
and was looking for her first title this year.
</P>
<P>
Spirlea ousted fourth-seeded Seles 6-4, 7-6 (7-5), and was also
seeking her first championship of the year. This was Spirlea's
second win out of six matches over Seles who won the tournament in
1991.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will battle Sanchez Vicario in one semifinal while
Davenport faces Spirlea on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
