<HEADLINE> More Private Firms Moving to North China Economic Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 4,000 private
businesses have moved to the Tianjin Economic Development Zone in
this port city, and they have an annual output value of 5 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, 1,300 private enterprises with a registered
capital of 1.6 billion yuan have been set up in the zone. And 80
of the private businesses have registered a capital exceeding 10
million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the private businesses in zone are in the
service sector, according to Tian Guiming, vice-director of the
zone's Administration Committee. He says the committee will make a
greater effort to encourage production-oriented and hi-tech
industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
