<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motorcycle Industrial Park Begins Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The Guangyang Motorcycle
Industrial Park started production recently in a high-tech
industrial development zone in Changzhou, in China's Jiangsu
province.
</P>
<P>
The 53.3-hectare park used 150 million US dollars in investment
and can produce 200,000 motorcycles a year.
</P>
<P>
One of the companies there, the Changzhou-KYMCO Motorcycle
Co. Ltd, was formed by Jiangsu, a Taiwan company and 25 other
motorcycle parts manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture has developed six different types of
motorcycles with funds and technology from Taiwan's KYMCO.
</P>
<P>
It is set to produce 120,000 motorcycles in 1998, and 360,000
motorcycles in 2000, and hopes to be able to manufacture 500,000
motorcycles a year after that. 
</P>
</TEXT>
