<HEADLINE> South Asian Countries Discusses Arbitration Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 15 (Xinhua) -- South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) member countries are working out an
arbitration pact and discussions are under way to arrive at a
consensus on various provisions of the agreement, the local press
said today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is likely to be signed shortly by all the seven
SAARC countries, namely, India, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Bangladesh,
Bhutan, the Maldives and Nepal.
</P>
<P>
