<HEADLINE> Russia Opposes Use of Force Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Russian First Deputy Foreign
Minister Igor Ivandor reiterated here today that Russia is against
the use of force against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Interfax news agency, Ivandor said a
constructive way should be found in implementing the U.N. Security
Council resolutions on Iraq's disarmament.
</P>
<P>
Any military action against Iraq must be taken with prior
approval from the Security Council, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ivandor called on Iraq to facilitate the work of U.N. weapons
inspectors, but said what Iraq has done in fulfilling Security
Council resolutions and destroying the banned weapons should be
looked at objectively.
</P>
<P>
Also on Friday, Russia's State Duma, the lower house of
parliament, approved a resolution that calls for measures other
than force in settling the current crisis. 
