<HEADLINE> 107 Kinds of Wild Animals Found in Hainan's Wuzhi Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, November 15 (Xinhua) -- A terrestrial animal
investigation group of south China's Hainan Province has
discovered 107 kinds of wild animals in the Wuzhi Mountain Nature
Reserve in the central part of the island province.
</P>
<P>
Rare animals including black bears, clouded leopards, sambars
and silver pheasants are listed among the 107 kinds of animals.
</P>
<P>
The provincial investigation group went through the nature
reserve from east to west between October 5 and 7 to conduct
investigation.
</P>
<P>
The investigation group believed that large animals like black
bears and clouded leopards scatter all over the nature reserve.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the discovery indicated that a complete ecological
system including a complicated food-chain exists in the Hainan
Wuzhi Mountain which guarantees balance between various kinds of
animals.
</P>
<P>
They suggested that protection efforts should focus on black
bears, clouded leopards and other kinds of animals and their
ecological environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
