<HEADLINE> Albania Mourns Boat Accident Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos
Nano and his Italian counterpart, Romano Prodi, today mourned the
death of more than 100 Albanian refugees in a boat collision.
</P>
<P>
On March 28, a refugee boat left southern Albanian port Vlore
for Italy with 117 Albanians on board sank in the Adriatic Sea
after colliding with an Italian warship. Only 34 people survived.
</P>
<P>
At the burial service, Prodi expressed regret over the
accident, and reiterated his country's wish to support Albania as
well as forge friendly relations between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Nano said he hopes the Vlore straits, the scene of the
accident, will become the basis for development of partnership
between Albania and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The last 52 bodies were returned to Albania earlier this week
following the salvage of the boat by Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
