<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Benefits From Controlling Soil Erosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, November 15 (Xinhua) -- The ten-year construction
project on the Fenhe River, located in north China's Shanxi
province, has not only effectively controlled erosion, but has
also helped local farmers escape poverty.
</P>
<P>
Residents in the Fenhe River Basin, especially areas in the
upper reaches of the river, long suffered from the effects of
severe soil erosion which not only led to poverty, but also
threatened the integrity of the Fenhe Reservoir and agricultural
and industrial production of the area.
</P>
<P>
Since 1988, the provincial government has invested 200 million
yuan (12.5 million U.S. dollars) in efforts to control soil
erosion in the upper reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
Soil erosion on some 150,000 ha in the upper reaches of the
river has primarily been controlled over the past decade. New
vegetation planted on 112,000 ha has effectively improved the
local ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
Some 31,000 ha of farmland in the upper reaches have been
reclaimed, and the per capita income of local farmers has jumped
to 1,000 yuan (125 US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971115.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Robberies Increase in Sao Paulo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The number of bank
robberies in the Brazilian city of Sao Paulo increased by 20.6
percent from January to September of this year over the same
period of 1996, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Press reports quoted the Public Security Secretariat of the
city as saying that 1,060 bank robberies were registered in the
first nine months of this year, while the number in 1996 was 879.
</P>
<P>
According to the Sao Paulo Banks Association, bank robbers
stole more than 50 million reals (almost as much in dollars) from
January to September of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Public Security Secretariat said that from September of
1995 to the same month of this year, there were 2,480 bank
robberies, and police have detained so far this year more than 400
robbers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
