<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Olympiakos Fined Heavily for Fans Disorder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The disciplinary commission of
the European soccer ruling body UEFA on Friday fined Greek side
Olympiakos 150,000 swiss francs (110,000 dollars) for their fans
disorder.
</P>
<P>
Olympiakos' fans threw smoke bombs and plastic bottles, one of
which hit a referee's assistant, during their Champions League
match with Real Madrid on November 5. The match ended 0-0.
</P>
<P>
UEFA also fined Dutch club Feyenoord 25,000 Swiss francs after
crowd disturbances at their Champions' League home tie against
Manchester United on November 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
