<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Investors Look to Processing Zone in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Investors are
negotiating with the Panamanian Regional Authority (ARI) over the
installation of a processing zone near Telfers Island.
</P>
<P>
Ricardo Duran, executive director of an organization called Pro
Panama, said today it was intended to sign contracts.
</P>
<P>
Duran highlighted the importance of investments from China. He
said an economic and commercial exhibition will be held on
November 18 with the participation of 73 firms from 14 Chinese
provinces and provincial-level cities.
</P>
<P>
Duran, who is in charge of promoting foreign investment in
Panama, said his office had been making great efforts to attract
investments from China.
</P>
<P>
"There is a renewed effort to attract Chinese entrepreneurs to
establish their enterprises of assembling and manufacturing
products to be reexported to the Latin American countries," said
Duran.
</P>
<P>
Trade between Panama and China amounts to 1.8 billion U.S.
dollars a year through the Colon Free Trade Zone, on the Atlantic
coast of Panama. 
</P>
</TEXT>
