<HEADLINE> Automation Technology Targets Growing Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Automation technology and
equipment, key elements in the nation's campaign to renovate large
and medium-sized state enterprises, will find a large and
enthusiastic market in China, experts said in today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
"The further development of automation technology will have
extensive prospects owing to China's sustained economic growth,"
said Zhang Yijun, vice-director of the Manufacturing Technology
Committee under the China Automation Association (CAA).
</P>
<P>
The country's loss-making state enterprises will carry out
large-scale technological renovation, as a result of the central
authority's determination to intensify reforms by means of merger
and the joint stock system.
</P>
<P>
"The automation technology will play a key role in this
campaign," an industrial expert said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that China need 100 units of large
distribution control systems (DCS) and 500 small DCS units
annually.
</P>
<P>
The country also sees high demand for programmable logic
controllers (PLC). More than 200 units of large PLC are ordered
annually, along with 2,000 units of medium-sized equipment and
20,000 units of small equipment.
</P>
<P>
"The demand for automation technology and equipment is very
strong, but the product quality should be given great attention,"
said Zhou Donghua, CAA vice-secretary general.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to improve the technology for industrial
automation and quality inspection, the China International
Automation and Quality Control Machinery and Equipment Exhibition
will be held in Beijing next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
