<HEADLINE> Latin American Cultural News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
items of culture, arts and entertainment news in the Latin
American countries in the past few days:
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- Delegates of scientific, political,
artistic and sports sectors from 16 American and African countries
were participating in the Second International Black Expression
Encounter in this capital.
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- The most representative works of painters,
sculptors, poets and artists of Nicaragua were displayed in the
hall of the Organization of American States (OAS) in Washington,
this week.
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- The First Festival of Contemporary Indian Cinema
opened in Costa Rica Wednesday. The festival will end on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- The 24th Traditional Handicrafts International
Exhibition was being held here, It opened on October 30.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen Latin American countries and the United States were
participating in this annual event. The central theme is "The
Presence of Animals in Traditional Handicrafts." The display ends
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- Four festivals of scenic arts were being held
simultaneously in Caracas and other Venezuelan cities. They
opened Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexican writer Octavio Paz, 1990 Nobel
Literature Prize winner, denied that he had died and said his
health was much better.
</P>
<P>
"I regret that those who strive to have me dead do it with such
a haste," said Paz.
</P>
<P>
An international news agency distributed a dispatch about the
death of the 83-year-old writer, though it immediately denied the
story and apologized for the mistake.
</P>
<P>
"Funeral harbingers never learn to smile. I would advise them
not to learn the art of dying, but the art of smiling," said the
Nobel laureate.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- A Canadian circus will visit Sao Paulo and Rio de
Janeiro on December 9-10. It will be the first Canadian troupe to
visit a Latin American country.
</P>
<P>
The circus includes acrobats, gymnasts and ballerinas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
