<HEADLINE> Sampras Edges out Rafter to Reach Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 14 (Xinhua) -- American Pete Sampras reached the
last four of the ATP Tour world tennis championship, beating
U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter 6-4, 6-1 in Hanover on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, Rafter and Carlos Moya all completed Red Group play at
2-1, with Moya and Sampras advancing based on better sets and
games differential.
</P>
<P>
The American world No. 1, whose tour-leading seven titles this
year include Wimbledon and the Australian Open, hit seven aces to
one for Rafter, and hit 28 winners against Rafter's 13.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, the first Australian in the season-ending event since
Pat Cash in 1987, has beaten Sampras only once, in 1993. Sampras
has won all eight meetings since then, the last three in straight
sets.
</P>
<P>
Sampras will play Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman, who beat
second-ranked American Michael Chang 6-4, 7-5 in the White Group.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman has jumped from No. 69 to No. 4 in the world after
winning three titles this year, including last week's tournament
in Stockholm.
</P>
<P>
Chang was making his sixth appearance in the championship. The
only time he advanced past the round-robin play was in 1995, when
he reached runner-up.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Moya, Australian Open runner-up, will face Yevgeny
Kafelnikov of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Bruguera, eliminated Thursday, withdrew from his last,
meaningless match against Kafelnikov with a back injury. The ATP
invited Tim Henman to replace him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
