<HEADLINE> Austrian President to Stand Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Incumbent Austrian President
Thomas Klestil said today that he will enter next year's
presidential elections to seek a second term of office.
</P>
<P>
The president, 65, said he will campaign as an independent
candidate without support by any political groups and the
government will not finance his candidature.
</P>
<P>
Klestil won the 1992 presidential elections as a candidate of
the Austria Peoples Party. His six-year term in office runs out
in July 1998, and the presidential elections are scheduled to be
held in February 1998.
</P>
<P>
To date, construction tycoon Richard Lugner and Heide Schmidt,
leader of the Liberal Forum party, have declared their plans to
stand for president. Candidates from the Social Democratic Party
and the Austrian Freedom Party are yet to be decided. 
</P>
