<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador On Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The universal
principles of human rights must be integrated with the specific
conditions of each country, Chinese Ambassador to the United
Nations Qin Huasun stressed here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Third Committee (Social, humanitarian and
cultural)of the fifty-second session of General Assembly on the
question of human rights, Qin Huasun said mankind is at present at
a historical turn of the century. International activities in the
field of human rights are also at a critical crossroad. Reviewing
the past helps us gain new insights.
</P>
<P>
Qin said in carrying out commemorative activities for the 50th
anniversary of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights and the
five-year review of the Vienna Declaration and program of
Action, the international society should carefully summarize
experience and lessons of the past and ensure the development of
human rights activities into the next century in a right
direction.
</P>
<P>
Qin said the universal principles of human rights must be
integrated with specific conditions of each country. The
universally recognized principles governing human rights result
from the development of human civilization, which are of positive
significance to the future development of mankind and applicable
to every member of the international community.
</P>
<P>
Qin said China is of the view that it is normal for countries
to have differences on the question of human rights. What is
important is how to deal with these differences. Practices have
proved as long as countries enter into dialogue on an equal
footing and on the principles of mutual respect and seeking
common ground while reserving differences, they will be able to
enhance understanding and narrow differences.
</P>
<P>
Qin said China is not in favor of practicing power politics,
exerting political and economic pressure on countries with
different views and imposing one's own ideology and values on
others in the field of human rights. There are more and more
countries supporting to handle the question of human rights
through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Qin said the international community should take practical and
effective measures to remove at the earliest possible date various
unfair and irrational phenomena in the international field of
human rights.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said in today's world, hegemonism and power
politics remains the major threat to world peace and stability.
The unfair and inequitable international economic order continues
to undermine the interests of developing countries. The gap
between the rich and the poor is further widening. War, poverty
and discrimination have deprived hundreds of millions of people of
their basic human rights.
</P>
<P>
Qin said a few countries use human rights as a political
instrument, pursue selectivity and double standards in the UN
human rights field and grossly interfere in the internal affairs
of developing countries. At the same time, economic, social and
cultural rights that developing countries are concerned about have
been long neglected and the implementation of the right to
development has long been delayed.
</P>
<P>
Qin called on the countries concerned to abandon prejudice and
self-interests and work together with developing countries to
reverse the current erroneous trend in the international field of
human rights and take effective measures to promote the global
realization of human rights and fundamental freedom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
