<HEADLINE> UNSCOM Chairman to Consult More with Security Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 14 (Xinhua) -- Richard Butler,
Chairman of the United Nations Special Commission in charge of
destroying Iraqi mass destruction weapons, promised here today
that he would consult more with the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the Security Council said Butler was strongly
criticized by several council members during Thursday
consultations for his not seeking Council's agreement before
making the decision to withdraw UN arms inspection staff from Iraq
starting Friday.
</P>
<P>
Butler said he would try to avoid this in the future and
consult more with the Security Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
