<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador on Control of Small Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 14 (Xinhua) -- The excessive accumulation
and illicit circulation of small arms and light weapons will greatly
worsen the situation and increase conflicts in the regions of turmoil,
Sha Zukang, Chinese ambassador on disarmament, said at the U.N.
headquarters here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Commission of the Disarmament and International
Security, Sha said that the illicit circulation of such arms will also
lead to expansion of terrorism and drug trafficking, hindering the
social and economic development in different regions.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese delegation is for a proper disposal of the
excessive accumulation of small arms and opposes resolutely any
countries' engagement in illicit circulation of any weapons, which
brutally interferes in the internal affairs of the sovereign countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese ambassador also noted that the just needs of relevant
countries in self-defense and security should be put into full
consideration, while exercising the weapon control.  
</P>
</TEXT>
