<HEADLINE> Chirac: Southeast Asia Financial Crisis Will Not </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 14 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
said today that he thinks the financial crisis in Southeast Asian
countries will not last long, as the fundamental balance sheet of
these economies are good.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think that this crisis would last long," said Chirac
in an interview with the Public Radios of the French Language
(CRPFL) during the Francophonie summit held today in Hanoi, Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that the crisis was caused by "the weakness of the
banking and financial system of certain countries, which is
particularly true for Thailand and Indonesia."
</P>
<P>
"But their balance sheets are good. What the experts call the
fundamental things, these are inflation, deficit of public finances,
the rate of growth. All these are good," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
