<HEADLINE> World Bank Chief Promotes Shengman Zhang as Managing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 14 (Xinhua) -- James D. Wolfensohn,
President of the World Bank today announced the appointment of
Shengman Zhang as Managing Director and Corporate Secretary of the
World Bank Group.
</P>
<P>
Zhang will be responsible for providing corporate management
and oversight in a number of key areas. In the process, he will
help take a more strategic and coherent approach to a number of
institution-wide functions which play a critical role in
supporting the operations of the World Bank Group.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, a Chinese national was chosen by Wolfensohn as his vice
president at the end of 1995, six months following he took up the
World Bank president.
</P>
<P>
Wolfensohn said Zhang is selected for his position "based on
his strategic judgement and Bank Group-wide perspective, his
proven management record, his high credibility with staff,
management, and the Executive Board, and his experience in
implementing World Bank-financed development projects in a
borrowing country."
</P>
<P>
Zhang is the first Chinese who has been promoted to the
high-ranking position in the World Bank's over 50 years of
history.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Zhang, other three Managing Directors include Sven
Sandstrom, Caio Koch-Weser and Jessica Einhorn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
